title: MSU at UM game will start at 3:30 p.m.
text:
Aaron Burbridge makes a catch while Jourdan Lewis covers during last year's game, won by MSU, 35-11. (Photo: Leon Halip, Getty Images) 
11 CONNECT 23 TWEET LINKEDIN 7 COMMENT EMAIL MORE The Michigan State at Michigan rivalry game on Saturday, Oct. 17 will begin at 3:30 p.m., it was announced Monday.
It will be televised by ABC, ESPN or ESPN2. TV coverage will be determined after this Saturday's games.
The Spartans (5-0) are ranked fourth in the Associated Press poll and the Wolverines (4-1) are No. 18.
Michigan State travels to Rutgers this Saturday night at 8 p.m. and Michigan is host to Northwestern at 3:30 p.m. Both games are on the Big Ten Network.
The Spartans have dominated the series in recent years, winning six of the last seven. That followed a 12-year stretch in which the Wolverines won 10 of 12 from 1996-2007.
